splash.splashContent:
Targets for Reducing Inequality in Canada

Use this app to explore the growth of lower income Canadian census subdivisions' median income from 2001 to 2016

Zoom or click to interact with map features

about.aboutContent: In 2015, the United Nations adopted the 17 SustainableDevelopment Goals, to serve as a roadmap for social and environmental prosperity into the future. Goal 10, to reduce inequality, sets targets to reduce income inequalityand foster economic growth. To reduce income inequality in Canada, the growth of lower income areas should exceed the national average, closing the gap between high and low income earners. This app measures Canada's economic development prior to the adoption of Goal 10 using the same indicators, highlighting Canada's current trajectory.
